    "## 2. PEP 8 Naming Conventions\n",
    "\n",
    "### What is PEP 8?\n",
    "**PEP 8** is Python's official style guide. It provides conventions for writing readable and consistent code. Following PEP 8 makes your code instantly recognizable as "Pythonic" and easier for other Python developers to understand.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Core Naming Conventions:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Type | Convention | Example | Notes |\n",
    "|------|------------|---------|-------|\n",
    "| **Variables** | `snake_case` | `patient_age` | Lowercase with underscores |\n",
    "| **Functions** | `snake_case` | `calculate_bmi()` | Lowercase with underscores |\n",
    "| **Constants** | `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` | `MAX_PATIENTS` | All caps with underscores |\n",
    "| **Classes** | `PascalCase` | `PatientRecord` | CapWords (not used in this milestone) |\n",
    "| **Private** | `_leading_underscore` | `_internal_value` | Indicates "internal use" |\n",
    "\n",
    "### The Rules:\n",
    "- ✅ **Be descriptive**: Names should explain purpose\n",
    "- ✅ **Be consistent**: Use same style throughout\n",
    "- ✅ **Be pronounceable**: Names you can say out loud\n",
    "- ✅ **Avoid single letters**: Except in very short loops (i, j, k)\n",
    "- ✅ **Avoid abbreviations**: `patient_name` not `pt_nm`\n",
    "- ✅ **Use verbs for functions**: `get_data()` not `data()`"
   ]
  },
