    "## 3. Writing Useful Comments\n",
    "\n",
    "### The Golden Rule of Comments:\n",
    "**Comments should explain WHY, not WHAT.**\n",
    "\n",
    "Good code is self-documenting - variable names and structure should make the WHAT clear. Comments should explain the WHY:\n",
    "- Why did you choose this approach?\n",
    "- What's the business logic behind this?\n",
    "- Are there any edge cases to be aware of?\n",
    "- Is there a workaround for a known issue?\n",
    "\n",
    "### When to Comment:\n",
    "✅ **DO comment:**\n",
    "- Complex algorithms or business logic\n",
    "- Non-obvious workarounds or hacks\n",
    "- External references or documentation links\n",
    "- Intent that isn't clear from code\n",
    "- TODO items or known issues\n",
    "\n",
    "❌ **DON'T comment:**\n",
    "- Obvious code (e.g., `x = x + 1  # Add 1 to x`)\n",
    "- What the code does (should be clear from names)\n",
    "- Outdated or incorrect comments\n",
    "- Commented-out code (delete it instead)\n",
    "- Every single line"
   ]
  },
