    "## 4. Common Readability Mistakes\n",
    "\n",
    "### Mistakes That Reduce Code Readability:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Cryptic Variable Names** - Single letters, abbreviations, unclear meaning\n",
    "2. **Over-commenting** - Comments on every line stating the obvious\n",
    "3. **Commented-out Code** - Leaving old code instead of deleting it\n",
    "4. **Misleading Comments** - Comments that don't match the code\n",
    "5. **Inconsistent Naming** - Mixing styles throughout the codebase\n",
    "6. **Magic Numbers** - Hardcoded values without explanation\n",
    "7. **Long Names** - Excessively long variable names\n",
    "\n",
    "### The Solutions:\n",
    "- Use descriptive, pronounceable names\n",
    "- Comment WHY, not WHAT\n",
    "- Delete code, don't comment it out\n",
    "- Keep comments current with code changes\n",
    "- Choose one naming style and stick to it\n",
    "- Use named constants for magic numbers\n",
    "- Balance descriptiveness with brevity"
   ]
